                            <comment id="13010787" author="knoguchi" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 17:35:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Duplicate of &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HADOOP-5749&quot; title=&quot;FsShell  forces creation of default filesystem object and incorrectly uses default filesystem in some places&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;HADOOP-5749&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;HADOOP-5749&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; ?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13010813" author="mattf" created="Thu, 24 Mar 2011 18:16:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Be careful with this one as we move to Federation, because the &quot;-fs&quot; command line option is currently the only way to direct the FSClient at a file system other than the default one, if any.  So if you might want your client to target one of several name services (federated namenodes), you have to use the -fs option or provide an alternative.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019099" author="jnp" created="Tue, 12 Apr 2011 22:54:17 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt; minor comments:&lt;br/&gt;
   1. The test has a few System.out.println, please use LOG instead.&lt;br/&gt;
   2. A commented assertTrue could be removed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;+1 for the patch pending hudson results.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13019490" author="boryas" created="Wed, 13 Apr 2011 18:54:16 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;addressed comments by Jitendra.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;@Matt. This patch doesn&apos;t change how -fs is handled. It tries to create FS only when it is needed and based on the path instead of default system. But when nothing else is available a default one will be created. (from conf or from -fs).&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
